body_html: There's a lot of mention of ProfilerState from here. Since it's an enum, there's nothing we can leak from our side. So unless we're using pybind incorrectly, the error would be indeed on the library.

body: There's a lot of mention of `ProfilerState` from [here](https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/master/torch/csrc/autograd/profiler.h#L158). Since it's an enum, there's nothing we can leak from our side. So unless we're using pybind incorrectly, the error would be indeed on the library.
